                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <h1 style="color: #f99b82;">Welcome!</h1>
                    <h2>Know More About Us</h2>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        We believe that a play, if set right in motion, continues being in motion like a gradually increasing fireball that engulfs the souls, hearts and minds of people over generations by enduring through the harsh transformations of Time.
                        But we also understand that our belief is basically your fantasy that you wish could turn true somehow. Well, we'd like to tell you that it can; with us, it can.
                    </p>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-warning">Contact Us</button>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <img src="http://themebubble.com/demo/marketingpro/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seo-slide.png" class="img-fluid" alt="">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="pt-5 pb-5">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row align-items-center">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <h2>Our Core Features</h2>
                    <hr>
                    <p>
                        When you create a play, you live two lives: the life of the play and the life of executing the play in the real world.
                        Your artistic self battles the former while your pragmatic self desperately struggles with the latter, because no matter how great artists we are, the practical challenges - the challenge of
                        actually crossing that turbulent river - baffles us to the extent of jeopardizing your Artistic Self. Even if you, somehow, you manage to put up a show, it's a one-off that doesn't get the run
                        it needs. And just because of money, lack of resources and efficient planners, the play's journey in motion comes to a halt like one tragedy.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Our objective is to not let that happen anymore. We take over your Pragmatic Self leaving you with the now-liberated Artistic Self,
                        so that while you break your sweat in the rehearsals we make sure that you get the stage you want for as long as you want.
                    </p>
                    <br />
                </div>
            </div>
